\par \pard\plain \s6\li360\sa31 \f2\fs16 The object of Minesweeper is to clear the board of mines as quickly as possible without stepping on a mine.  The following section explains how to play the game.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Choose a Skill Level:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose Beginner, Intermediate, or Expert.  The higher the skill level, the larger the mine field.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Start a New Game:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Game menu, choose New, or press F2.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Step on a Square:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Point to the square, and click the left mouse button.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Clear Around a Square:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Point to the square, and click both the left and right mouse buttons.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  You can only clear around an uncovered square.  See "Rules of the Game" for more information. 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To {\ul Mark}{\v Mark} a Square:
\par \pard\plain \s7\fi-360\li720\sa180\tx720 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Point to the square, and click the right mouse button.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  To remove a mark, point to the square and click the right mouse button again.
